Following a tanker explosion at Chibyno filling station along Alaoji-Ikot-Ekpene Road Obingwa Local Government Area in Abia State, two men have been confirmed dead. Aba Fire Service Zonal Commander, Belenta Belenta who confirmed the incident to the NAN said the victims were suspected to be involved in oil bunkering as they were discharging petroleum products before daybreak. The official confirmed that five trucks were consumed by the fire caused by the explosion at the site. Belenta said personnel of the service eventually put out the inferno after mobilization.[1:04 pm, 08/06/2022] Mr Ajiboye INL: Go.